			<div class="content" id="post-content-4788948">
									

<p>thank you croq and nyaly for critique. thank you croq again for throwing everything together and leading the team</p>
<p>i am going to not look at the wiki for a week now</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">what&nbsp;is&nbsp;this&nbsp;getting&nbsp;at</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">done&nbsp;writing&nbsp;declassified&nbsp;article</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>in <em>this take</em>, the Occult Initiative/GOC created God/Physics/Reality, and their new forms could never understand this, so today, in their ignorance, they are constantly chasing their tails. so things like grass or blue skies, people, dogs and cats, etc, which were formerly unfathomable, are normal now. they can't fix reality, reality is trashed already</p>
<p>it doesn't matter who this is narrated by, but it might be safe to assume theyre a remnant of an old world.</p>
<p>this is framed as a meta-gutenberg book because this would fly over anyone's radar in universe, aside from the mention of the Initiative</p>
<p>the format is inspired by <a href="https://www.pdf-archive.com/2015/02/21/deathconsciousness-booklet/deathconsciousness-booklet.pdf">DEATHCONSCIOUSNESS</a> by have a nice life, my favorite faux-nonfiction writing</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>this is a canon entry and not a series. our contest articles are related insomuch that they take place during a specific part of the canon timeline</p>
